channel.title: Earbuds Recommendations
channel.description:
In this post, I will review and also ask for earbuds. If you guys know of any noise cancelling, comfortable, and good quality earbuds, let me know.
Now for the reviews. - I got two Skullcandy Smokin Buds 2 earbuds and they were pretty okay. Greatest quality I ever had and is comfortable and noise cancelling but one of the earbuds stopprd working in a month. - I got a Jlabs Metal earbud pack last week and they were okay too. Sometimes they're a bit loose and one side of the earbuds was stuffy unless I adjusted it in my ear. The quality is good too and they are somewhat noise cancelling if you fit the earbuds in. - I got the Jlabs Jbuds and expected something good. They werent really noise cancelling and they kinda hurt my ears when I tried to fit them in. The quality was okay.
I couldnt choose between metal or smokin buds 2 for the best

item.dc:creator: Arimyth
item.description:
Jax:

I‚Äôve noticed the sound quality has significantly dropped since I‚Äôve got them. Regular apple earbuds with wires have better quality then they do now. I think it‚Äôs part of apple downgrading it since the release of AirPods series 2

This is purely due to either the volume settings on your specific device or any wear and tear they‚Äôve endured while you‚Äôve owned them. Apple does not downgrade / throttle old hardware with the release of new hardware (besides the case of the 6/6s battery throttling), especially given that they haven‚Äôt actually pushed any new firmware to the Airpods which would render it impossible to intentionally modify their behavior at least through software.

@Hum4n01d Personally, I use Airpods for music production if I‚Äôm not near my wired headset and find the audio quality to be decent and any latency to be negligible especially given the lack of a live recording interface.
